    <title>Preferences - Metadata Handler</title>
    <p>
        The following image displays the Metadata Handler preferences dialog:
    </p>
    
    <figure>
        <desc>The Metadata Handler preferences dialog</desc>
        <media type="image" src="Images/preferences-metadata-handler.png"/>
    </figure>
    

        <p>
            This dialog allows you to control the large amount of metadata handlers, which are available either in GMPC directly or can be installed as plugins.
        </p>
        
        <terms>
            <title>The table offers the following configurable columns:</title>
            <item>
                <title>Enabled</title>
                <p>Check or uncheck this field if to enable or disable the respective metadata handler. If it offers a further configuration dialog, it will appear appear below the "Plugins:" menu point in GMPC's Preferences window.</p>
            </item>
            <item>
                <title>Priority</title>
                <p>When you click this field while the row is selected you can edit this value. The priority sets, in which order metadata handlers are queried. The value can be between 0 and 100 and priorities are evaluated from low to high.</p>
            </item>
        </terms>

